.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Input \- Bitcoin transaction input instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto qw(btc_transaction);
\&
\&        my $tx = btc_transaction\->new;
\&
\&        $tx\->add_input(
\&                utxo => [$txid, $output_index],
\&        );
\&
\&        print $tx\->inputs\->[0]\->dump;
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is an input instance implementation used in transactions. It is rarely
interacted with directly.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
\fIutxo\fR
.IX Subsection "utxo"
.PP
An instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::UTXO. Required.
.PP
Can also be passed an array reference of two parameters, which will be fed to
"get" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::UTXO to fetch the UTXO instance. It will
be done lazily, so that you can freely deserialize transactions without the
need to set up their UTXOs.
.PP
\&\fIAvailable in the constructor\fR.
.PP
\fIutxo_location\fR
.IX Subsection "utxo_location"
.PP
An array reference with the same data as passed to
"get" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::UTXO. Will be pulled out of whatever was
passed to "utxo".
.PP
\fIsignature_script\fR
.IX Subsection "signature_script"
.PP
The script used to unlock the coins from the UTXO.
.PP
By default, it is an empty script.
.PP
\&\fIAvailable in the constructor\fR.
.PP
\&\fIwriter\fR: \f(CW\*(C`set_signature_script\*(C'\fR
.PP
\fIsequence_no\fR
.IX Subsection "sequence_no"
.PP
Also known as \f(CW\*(C`nSequence\*(C'\fR in Bitcoin Core. The sequence number used in various
applications. Non\-negative integer.
.PP
By default, it is set to \f(CW0xffffffff\fR (\f(CW\*(C`max_sequence_no\*(C'\fR in \f(CW\*(C`Bitcoin::Crypto::Constants\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\&\fIAvailable in the constructor\fR.
.PP
\&\fIwriter\fR: \f(CW\*(C`set_sequence_no\*(C'\fR
.PP
\fIwitness\fR
.IX Subsection "witness"
.PP
SegWit data for this input. It is an array reference of bytestrings. Note that
each element in the witness must be a separate element in this array
(concatenating the witness into one bytestring will not work as intended).
.PP
Empty by default.
.PP
\&\fIAvailable in the constructor\fR.
.PP
\&\fIwriter\fR: \f(CW\*(C`set_witness\*(C'\fR
.PP
\&\fIpredicate\fR: \f(CW\*(C`has_witness\*(C'\fR
.SS Methods
.IX Subsection "Methods"
\fInew\fR
.IX Subsection "new"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $input = $class\->new(%args)
.Ve
.PP
This is a standard Moo constructor, which can be used to create the object. It
